The position starts in September 2017 and ends in Septembre 2020. The =
candidate will pursue a PhD project in the ANR project Choucas involving =
3 Research Centers, the Computer Science Lab. of the Pau and Pays de =
l=E2=80=99Adour University, France (LIUPPA) (location of the position), =
the COGIT Lab. of the French National Institute of Geographic and Forest =
Information (IGN) and the Grenoble Informatics Lab. (LIG) in =
collaboration with the National Gendarmerie with its special Hight =
Mountain unit (PGHM).
The project Choucas =C2=AB Integration of heterogeneous data and spatial =
reasoning for helping to locate victims in the mountains =C2=BB, is a =
pluridisciplinary project that bridges three research themes: =
structuring and interrogation of heterogeneous data, fuzzy spatial =
reasoning and geovisualization of imperfect geographical data.


Le travail de th=C3=A8se s=E2=80=99int=C3=A9ressera en particulier =C3=A0 =
la partie textuelle non structur=C3=A9e des donn=C3=A9es et =C3=A9tablir =
un pont entre la th=C3=A9orie spatio-linguistique, les approches =
d=E2=80=99analyse et de traitement des donn=C3=A9es spatiales, le =
traitement probabiliste pilot=C3=A9 par les donn=C3=A9es et l'analyse =
s=C3=A9mantique. La nouveaut=C3=A9 de l=E2=80=99approche consiste =C3=A0 =
mettre la s=C3=A9mantique spatiale au centre de la mod=C3=A9lisation, =
mettant l'accent sur l'adoption d'une approche de construction de la =
grammaire en utilisant par exemple des grammaires d=E2=80=99arbres =
adjoints.
Le travail de th=C3=A8se s=E2=80=99int=C3=A9ressera =C3=A9galement =C3=A0 =
la correspondance d'informations extraites du texte avec la g=C3=A9om=C3=A9=
trie d'une ou de plusieurs traces GPS associ=C3=A9es. L'originalit=C3=A9 =
de cet objectif r=C3=A9side dans la d=C3=A9finition d'un processus =
d'appariement de donn=C3=A9es tr=C3=A8s h=C3=A9t=C3=A9rog=C3=A8nes: le =
texte et les g=C3=A9om=C3=A9tries. Cela n=C3=A9cessitera d'abord le =
traitement g=C3=A9om=C3=A9trique et la mod=C3=A9lisation des traces GPS =
pour extraire leurs caract=C3=A9ristiques spatiales, ce qui peut =C3=AAtre=
 consid=C3=A9r=C3=A9 comme un probl=C3=A8me de raisonnement spatial =
qualitatif. Cela peut alors s'appuyer sur des techniques d'optimisation, =
comme celle utilisant des mod=C3=A8les de Markov cach=C3=A9s pour faire =
correspondre les traces GPS et les donn=C3=A9es routi=C3=A8res pour la =
navigation automobile.

Le traitement probabiliste pilot=C3=A9 par les donn=C3=A9es sera =
r=C3=A9alis=C3=A9 en collaboration avec le laboratoire de math=C3=A9matiqu=
es et d'applications. De Pau, France (LMAP).

The PhD project is in particular concerned with the unstructured textual =
part of the data and the bridges between spatio-linguistic theory and =
spatial data processing approaches and data-driven probabilistic =
processing and semantic parsing. The novelty of its approach consists in =
putting spatial-semantics as the modeling focal point, putting an =
emphasis on adopting a constructional approach to grammar by using =
tree-based grammar frameworks.=20
The PhD project is also concerned with the matching of information =
extracted from the text to the geometry of one or several associated GPS =
tracks. The originality of this goal lies in the definition of a =
matching process of very heterogeneous data: text and geometries. This =
will first require the geometric processing and modeling of GPS tracks =
to extract their spatial characteristics, which may be thought of as a =
qualitative spatial reasoning issue. This may then rely on optimization =
techniques, like the one using Hidden Markov Models to match GPS tracks =
and road data for car navigation.

The data-driven probabilistic processing will be conduct in cooperation =
with the Mathematics and Its Applications Lab. of Pau, France (LMAP).


